    "body": "### Neovim Version\n\nv0.5.0\n\n### Operating system/version:\n\nmacOs 11.4\n\n### Terminal name/version:\n\niTerm 3.4.8\n\n### TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nEnter nvim via either `nvim -u NORC` or `nvim -u NONE`. Then execute:\r\n\r\n```\r\n:set listchars=tab:‚óÄÔ∏é‚îÅ‚ñ∂Ô∏é\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error message that shows is:\r\n\r\n```\r\nE474: Invalid argument: listchars=tab:‚óÄÔ∏é‚îÅ‚ñ∂Ô∏é\r\n```\r\n\r\nNotably, the same command works as expected in `vim -u DEFAULTS`.\n\n### Vim\n\nVIM - Vi IMproved 8.2, macOS version - x86_64, Included patches: 1-3150\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTabs should be listed as `‚óÄÔ∏é‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚îÅ‚ñ∂Ô∏é`\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nnvim gives `E474`\r\n\r\nvim behaves correctly",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@danielyli  It seems that your tab option actually contains five chars, there are two variation selections (`U+FE0E`) not visible, but they are there.\r\n\r\nI tried to remove the two `U+FE0E`, then the tab setting works.\r\n\r\n```\r\nset list listchars=tab:‚óÄ‚îÅ‚ñ∂\r\n```",
